      }
    },
    {
      "key": "691409b7-bf02-40b5-8a3f-c003d7f0db37",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **(Optional) Do This:** Have students complete as many Create levels as they can.",
        "progression_name": "Create",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "**High Ceiling:**\nCreate levels provide opportunities for enrichment for students who complete the progression early or are looking for additional challenges. These levels go above the core concepts from the lesson and should be considered \"extra\". There is always a \"free play\" create level for students who want a more open-ended experience in building their songs.\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "691409b7-bf02-40b5-8a3f-c003d7f0db37",
        "lesson_activity.key": "88135275-ed13-4b53-8e83-be9091de2536"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8956c5cb-0e8b-4fc8-bfac-17e344db4368",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa-solid fa-headphones\"></i> **Listen**: As a class, listen to the first minute of [Sun by Caribou](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4Uez8NNFf9s) without showing students any information about the song.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Write down 5 words that describe this song. You could pick words that describe the genre or musicality, or that describe it's \"vibe\" or how it feels.\n\nDo not ask students to share out yet - instead continue to the next song.\n\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-headphones\"></i> **Listen**: As a class, listen to the first minute of [Sun (Only what you gave me remix) by Altrice](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y_dgMAPaJLM) without showing students any information about the song.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Write down 5 words that describe this song. You could pick words that describe the genre or musicality, or that describe it's \"vibe\" or how it feels.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Using the words you wrote down, how were these two songs different? How were they similar?\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Have students share their similarities and differences, emphasizing that the \"feel\" of the song may be different between them even if some of the more superficial details are the same (ie: is an \"electronic\" song, has repeating beats). If students begin to suspect they're remixes of the same song, ask them to clarify and justify why they think this.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> These two songs are actually very similar - the second song is a remix of the first one. The remix was done by a remix artist named Altrice using the exact same tracks from the original song in a completely new and original way. Today, we're going to apply what we've been learning to create remixes similar to how Altrice does."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8956c5cb-0e8b-4fc8-bfac-17e344db4368",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7c3b82a0-fc07-45c4-9d7e-8fb01146856a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "858724d2-acae-4111-9cc9-cc39ddbd1b26",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> We're going to start with a quick review of some skills from this week and a check-in level. Once you've passed the check-in, we'll continue to learn more about Altrice and how he creates remixes.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "**Opportunity for Differentiation:** These first few levels are designed to provide an opportunity for differentiation or individual intervention. Students who may have been absent or struggling so far can spend additional time in these levels (or revisiting previous assessments) before continuing to the rest of the lesson. Otherwise, students can complete the quick check-in to reinforce the skills from this unit and then continue to the career spotlight."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "858724d2-acae-4111-9cc9-cc39ddbd1b26",
        "lesson_activity.key": "aefc5603-3822-4074-a706-9a53f0bbfc67"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "debcfc6a-1c80-42d7-9525-8c63f637e8a0",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students log into the Skill Review level. These levels are a review of all of the skills students have seen in the last two lessons. \n- If students feel confident in what they've been learning, have them continue to the Check-In level.\n- If students have been absent or need a review, have them review the sublevels before continuing to the Check-In",
        "progression_name": "Skill Review"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "debcfc6a-1c80-42d7-9525-8c63f637e8a0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "aefc5603-3822-4074-a706-9a53f0bbfc67"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "654f2693-2b5f-4907-ae12-860d2fe14719",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete the Check-In",
        "progression_name": "Check-In",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "**Formative Assessment**: This level is the last assessment before the mini-project in the next lesson - consider checking the level during class and providing targeted intervention if students are struggling. Ideally any lingering issues can be addressed here before continuing to the more open-ended project and the rest of the unit."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "654f2693-2b5f-4907-ae12-860d2fe14719",
        "lesson_activity.key": "aefc5603-3822-4074-a706-9a53f0bbfc67"
      }
    },
